Package grafioschtrader.repository

Interface GTNetJpaRepository

All Superinterfaces:
BaseRepositoryCustom<GTNet>, org.springframework.data.repository.CrudRepository<GTNet,Integer>, GTNetJpaRepositoryCustom, org.springframework.data.jpa.repository.JpaRepository<GTNet,Integer>, org.springframework.data.repository.ListCrudRepository<GTNet,Integer>, org.springframework.data.repository.ListPagingAndSortingRepository<GTNet,Integer>, org.springframework.data.repository.PagingAndSortingRepository<GTNet,Integer>, org.springframework.data.repository.query.QueryByExampleExecutor<GTNet>, org.springframework.data.repository.Repository<GTNet,Integer>, UpdateCreateJpaRepository<GTNet>
public interface GTNetJpaRepository extends org.springframework.data.jpa.repository.JpaRepository<GTNet,Integer>, GTNetJpaRepositoryCustom, UpdateCreateJpaRepository<GTNet>
Repository for managing GTNet domain configurations. Provides CRUD operations for remote domain entries plus specialized queries for:
  • Finding broadcast targets (domains accepting entity or price requests)
  • Finding active price providers (for consumer-side queries)
  • Looking up domains by URL (for handshake processing)
See Also:
  • for complex operations like message submission

  • Method Details

    • findByAcceptEntityRequestOrAcceptLastpriceRequest

      List<GTNet> findByAcceptEntityRequestOrAcceptLastpriceRequest(boolean acceptEntityRequest, boolean acceptLastpriceRequest)
      Finds domains that accept either entity or lastprice requests. Used to determine broadcast targets for maintenance announcements and shutdown notices.
      Parameters:
      acceptEntityRequest - true to include domains accepting entity requests
      acceptLastpriceRequest - true to include domains accepting lastprice requests
      Returns:
      list of domains matching either criterion

    • findByLastpriceConsumerUsageAndLastpriceServerState

      List<GTNet> findByLastpriceConsumerUsageAndLastpriceServerState(byte lastpriceConsumerUsage, byte lastpriceServerState)
      Finds domains that match both the given consumer usage priority and server state. Used to find active price providers when this instance acts as a consumer. Note: The parameter names suggest a bug - lastpriceConsumerUsage should probably be "greater than" rather than "equals", and the query should find providers with SS_OPEN state.
      Parameters:
      lastpriceConsumerUsage - the priority level (0 = not used, higher = used with priority)
      lastpriceServerState - the required server state (typically SS_OPEN = 4)
      Returns:
      list of domains matching both criteria

    • findByDomainRemoteName

      GTNet findByDomainRemoteName(String domainRemoteName)
      Looks up a domain by its URL. Used during handshake processing to check if a remote domain is already known, and to find the matching entry when receiving M2M requests.
      Parameters:
      domainRemoteName - the full base URL (e.g., "https://example.com:8080")
      Returns:
      the matching GTNet entry, or null if not found
